Q. Did you see the mother that day or not - A. I did not see her at our house. The constable accused Eleanor of it; she persisted in denying that she had been in the room. We afterwards went to her mother, the officer told her mother for what purpose we came. I was present when the bank note was found in her pocket; we found the lace in a box;
Eleanor Flynn
said she found the lace in a room.
